author: notonft
content:
**Happy 2025 @everyone ! We‚Äôre heading into the new year with a number of important announcements.**

It‚Äôs been a wild couple of years in NFTs. As a reminder, since minting to a larger collection Turtles:‚Ä®‚Ä®
- Deployed a unique NFT staking platform which provided real value back to owners
- Deployed a fractionalization platform for difficult to find assets and supported some of the OG Solana projects when everyone said the network was dead
- Created a custom merch line with smart contract capable of accepting SPL tokens, which were given freely to NFT stakers
- Launched Ordinals collectibles with sub-1M inscription numbers
- Countless other small, daily releases to try and push the Turtles NFT narrative forward

We will again have development resources in February 2025. The fractionalization platform IP is now owned by a firm adequately funded and staffed to address the legal and regulatory hurdles of operating it.

In 2025 Turtles NFT will return to simple community driven participation and support of the Solana ecosystem. I would have done a lot of things differently, if I could go back. But since I can‚Äôt, I am reaffirming commitment to continuing the Turtles IP no matter where we are in the cycle, which chain is hot, or what the current meta is.

All unrevealed Turtles will be revealed automatically in the coming weeks, and we will begin a community push once more focused on lore, memes, history, and our support of Solana when nobody else wanted to be here.

**Deals update:**

This information is not meant for citizens or tax residents of the United States.

A low tech framework provided by the IP owners will safely close out deal tokens. I believe everyone will be happy with the end, even though it is taking a long time in web3 terms. Turtles Discord cannot provide information beyond directing you to the appropriate areas. Please do not post Personally Identifiable Information in this Discord or in DMs to community managers.

The next chapters starts now. Deal token holders must begin by confirming wallets here: https://forms.gle/qCb8EqXq3hwrY7Md7

author: notonft
content:
GM @everyone. It‚Äôs been a while since I gave you a project update. NFTs are down bad, and the feeling is it‚Äôs never coming back. As always in web3, the most entertaining outcome is the most likely...

**Project/Community**
Slow and steady wins the race‚Ä¶

Since the meta shifted to meme coins, NFTs and Discord communities have been dead. But if you haven‚Äôt checked into Alpha Hut in a while you should, because I see 3-5 quality calls each week. There are still opportunities, and the OGs that have been chilling here for 3 years have experience edge.

**Deals**
We have devised a way to manually address deal tokens with no smart contract risk, and will be implementing that system.  I expect things to move along before the end of the year. In case it was not clear before, we will not have access to new deals through holding NFTs. At this time please do not move tokens from wallets or OTC trade unless absolutely necessary, as this will create complication later.

**Wen Turtles?**
The team is still here, and if NFTs ever come back Turtles will mean something. There are no staking or other web3 development plans as of today. A while ago I said it was time to move to web2 for a wider audience, and I'm still sticking to that. Right now we're just vibing, looking for opportunities, and watching for whatever meta comes next.

**As always, Turtles are fck.**

Hi @everyone, we opened the reveal portal early at https://reveal.turtles.vc and was hit so hard it began having issues updating the collection image data, resulting in duplicate images. **We are pausing the update portal while we make sure we can handle mass transactions  better! Update to come in the next 12 hours. We will share in advance the time reveal will begin again.**

**FULL DETAIL**

After final testing on mainnet was occurring the link to reveal was leaked, and so we decided lfg. I shared the link on a Twitter space and then people began revealing. Over 300 reveals were processed in the first 10 minutes, but our program started to choke. There are a number of issues we are double checking for all users who processed reveal transactions:

**- TRTLS were taken but reveal did not happen.** In most cases the reveal has happened and Phantom has not updated. We are reviewing each transaction to be sure.

**- Duplicate images.** We have identified 20 NFTs that had "slipped" transactions and got assigned the wrong image. In this case they will be updated after putting a fix in place.

**WEN**

**- Staking 2.0. **After we are rolling again on reveal, likely 24 hours after reveal portal is back live.

**- Turtle NFT Airdrop. **To get the airdrop you will need to reveal and stake to validate the wallet and NFT. We will then airdrop an unrevealed Turtle. 3-5 days after staking goes live.

**- Refund for reveal fee from Turtles Classic.** Any converted Turtle will get the airdrop. This will happen 1-2 days AFTER the above NFT airdrop.

content:
**Our collection update portal is now LIVE @everyone! https://update.turtles.vc** You will receive one of 3 tiers of rarity bonus. Public mint will have a 4th common tier, so there are advantages to sweeping the floor and capturing the last cheap turtles as they will all get a significant rarity boost for reveal.

**STEP 1:** Unstake your Turtles from https://turtles.vc
**STEP 2:** Visit https://update.turtles.vc and connect wallet
**STEP 3: **Select your Turtles and click CONVERT
**STEP 4:** Wait for your transaction to process. New Turtles will be placed in your wallet

You may move your current Turtle NFTs to the new collection at any time. We strongly suggest doing so as soon as possible to avoid any problems at mint time. **We will be ending staking rewards until post mint.**

**What happens next?**

In a few days, the current Turtles collection name will be updated to Turtles Classic.

Our newly minted collection will take on the name Turtles beginning on Magic Eden and filtering out to major exchanges over the next week. Please double check when trading Turtles.

Our collection update portal will remain open for the next 30 days. After that, the portal will close and you will not be able to transfer Turtles Classic NFTs to the new collection.

**What about outstanding loans on FRAKT and Sharky?**

Taking out loans on Turtles Classic NFTs will be disabled, and any outstanding loans will need to be paid in order to use the collection update portal.

**I don‚Äôt want my NFTs to change. What are my options?**

You do NOT have to transfer your NFT to the new collection, however you will not receive rewards access and platform benefits for Turtles Classic, including USDC staking rewards. We will create a special Discord role for anyone holding Turtles Classic only, offering the same access as a holder with 1 new NFT.

Please know the risks of leaving your NFT in Turtles Classic. The creator wallet credentials have passed through multiple SaaS platforms and devs over a 2 year period. We cannot guarantee the old collections are safe from bad actors.

**Are you going to do something cool for Turtles Classic in the future?**

We will revisit Turtles Classic utility in the future, but we will not be offering special incentives or surprises. Our goal is to move 100% of holders over to the new Turtles collection. There will not be airdrops, special access, or financial benefits for holding Turtles Classic at this time.

We love the old collections for the memories and respect anyone who wishes to keep their NFT unchanged.

author: Community Updates#0000
content:
Hey Admins and Mods!

In our mission to help you keep your communities safe and lift some of that moderation work off your shoulders, we‚Äôve set our sights on helping you more easily detect and prevent spam and raids. Today's spotlight introduces new features that help keep your communities cleaner from spam, and a preview into our early plans on building tools to deal with raids.

<:automod:978473808623194143> **Keep your Community clean from spam with new AutoMod spam filters**
We know dealing with spammy messages sucks. If *only* there was a way spammy messages could be blocked from being posted in your channels and threads in the first place‚Ä¶ 

Thankfully, every community‚Äôs best friend in moderation - **AutoMod** - just got buffed with some new spam-cleansing abilities. Enable AutoMod in **Server Settings > AutoMod** to save hours of moderation work with these new filters:
<:dot:890738617130037318>**Block Mention Spam** - Detect and block mention spam and mention raids before they happen to keep chat clean and prevent members in your community from receiving annoying mention notifications and ghost pings. Set your own limit on the number of mentions a message may contain (up to 50). 
<:dot:890738617130037318> **Block Spam Content** - Detect and block messages containing text content that has been widely flagged as spam by user reports. Great for blocking unwanted spam like those pesky free Nitro scams, unsolicited advertisements, and invite spam that disrupt your Community's friendly conversations and game nights.
Check out our updated AutoMod FAQ help article: https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/4421269296535-AutoMod-FAQ

**Our early plans and progress to protect communities from raids**
We know being raided is one of the worst experiences you and your Community can go through which is why we‚Äôre giving you a heads up that we‚Äôre exploring ways to better detect and prevent raids before they take place, while making it easier to de-escalate a raid when they do happen.

While we‚Äôre in the earlier stages of progress here at Discord Labs‚Ñ¢, rest assured we‚Äôre eager to equip you with effective tools to more easily deal with raids as quickly as we can. So what can you do now?
<:dot:890738617130037318> **Report Raids**: You can now directly send us feedback reports when a raid is taking place in your server by going to your Server Dropdown and selecting Report Raid. If your Community is being raided, we encourage you to partner with us in our moderation efforts by reporting the situation as we‚Äôll be regularly reviewing your raid reports to develop tooling that combat raids. 
<:dot:890738617130037318> **Pause invitations** to your Community at anytime - You can now pause your invite links for when you want to temporarily prevent people from joining your server without having to revoking your invite links or vanity URLs - just head over to **Server Settings > Invites**. 
Because this cuts off the flow of new arrivals, you'll have an easier time halting a raid in progress. It also lets well-intentioned community members trying to join know that the stoppage is temporary, and that soon, they‚Äôll be able to come back to the same link and try again.
Learn more about pausing invites: https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/8458903738647

**How we‚Äôre protecting communities from suspicious links: **
To help y‚Äôall with the legwork in dealing with messages containing malicious links, we‚Äôve buffed every Community server with a proactive suspicious link filter designed to detect and block messages containing links that are verified to be harmful, such as those leading to malware or phishing sites that try to steal people‚Äôs personal or financial information. We‚Äôll be continuously working on identifying links that might mislead or redirect users by reviewing a regularly updated list of unsafe and phishing websites: https://support.discord.com/hc/en-us/articles/7326747355159-Why-was-my-message-not-delivered-

1- Go https://solcasino.io
2- Open your wallet on Sol network (phantom,sollet whatever) and connect to the solcasino.io
3- Deposit your TRTLS from your wallet (still in solana network)

5- Add TRTLS to your metamask wallet.
6- Open https://earn.turtles.so, stake your TRTLS and start to earn USDC. @everyone

author: fiyopi
content:
Hello buddies,
Let me know what happened, what are we doing right now. 

Our dev was only one guy and when you had one dev, it‚Äôs risky for the whole project. When i‚Äôm saying one dev it‚Äôs about backend, i‚Äôm not couting artist&frontend devs etc., without backend guy, other things are not important. We are working since August, clearly we exhausted and for a couple months we didn‚Äôt even have a life because of devolepment, and the dev leaved me. Maybe it became because floor dropped 15-20 to 3 Sol. If someone doesn‚Äôt want to work anymore, i can‚Äôt do anything about that.

So after this i decided to hire different devs for the project.

We hired 3 different crews for our development.

1 - Generating Upgraded Turtles files (Our project is different than others, because we have complex traits, there are conditions and there are 2 sexs.
- This one is completed. 

2- New NFT Staking System
Second crew is working for this milestone. All nfts are staying in your wallet and also there are all claim, all stake buttons .
This one is completed too.

3- Upgrading System
The upgrading system will work with 2 stages.
I can‚Äôt give more details but will be airdrop for this system.
The dev who prepared staking system, also will build this system. 
It‚Äôs not ready yet.

4- Raffle System
Third crew is working for this milestone.
With the raffle system we will do WL raffles, NFT raffles, special 1/1 Turtle Nft raffles etc. 
The raffle system will be ready in a week according the third crew.

Without raffle and nft staking system or turtles token staking (farming USDC), we didn‚Äôt want to release our new nft staking system. Because it‚Äôs pointless having tokens untill those are available.

5- For Token Staking for USDC farming, this is a little bit hard for me, but i have a friend who is using this system on BSC. because of that i‚Äôm thinking to create a bridge to BSC chain and with bridge we can do easily that. First focus raffle&upgrading system after that i will focus this one.

There can be mistakes on sentences, i wrote without double check. Have a great day buddies. @everyone <@&891618254320205855> <@&904069127453409311> <@&911400902026465350>

author: shu02636
content:
Is important to make some rules for the Alpha-hut since the we have seen recent growth in the Turtles community and some people want to take advantage of this.

Alpha-hut is not a pump and dump telegram chat group.  If you have such a mentality about this channel, you must change your mind, or leave.  It is important to maintain the integrity of this channel.

We will put some rules to assure we have a real alpha channel for good projects that will benefit Turtle holders.

Rules:

1. Don't shill a project a project if you haven't done proper research about it.  Turtles are not babysitters to tell you if is good or not.  Posting discord links without an accompanying investment thesis will result in you being publicly shamed.

2. Talk about projects that you want to hold. If you talk about a project, it's because you want Turtles to hold as a DAO.

3. If you share a project and the community checks in and they realizes it is an obvious scam/cash-grab/worthless project, you will no longer be able to post in alpha-hut.

4. If you are part of the dev team, or have any affiliation whatsoever with the dev team, of a project you are shilling - you must state your affiliation as to avoid any conflict of interest.

5. Be intelligent.  Don't mint every trash project that comes your way. Alpha-hut is to make money, not to lose it. (DAH)
 
We will be introducing a new role: Alpha-insiders.  Alpha-insiders will help spot and share high quality projects with the Turtles community.

Alpha-insider role are the only one can share links on the alpha-hut channel.  Other members can use the alpha-proposal channel to shill other projects. (We will vote there) If a member shills good alpha, they may be given the role Alpha-insiders via voting.  Nominations for this position will be made by the Council, and voted on by all Turtle holders.

The ability to post in alpha-hut and the alpha-insider role can be removed from any member, without cause, upon resolution by the Council.  You may make an appeal to the Council explaining the situation, and if the Council is satisfied you may be reinstated. 

@everyone
